%N A395597 Decimal expansion of the aspect ratio of a rectangle with the property that a straight line drawn through a uniformly random point on one of the two larger sides, with direction chosen uniformly at random, intersects each of the three other sides with an equal probability.
%C A395597 The unique real solution to the equation 2*arctan(x) - log(1 + x^2)/x = Pi/3.
%e A395597 1.263122213969262542026249040522580451860297573323877...
%t A395597 RealDigits[r /. FindRoot[2*ArcTan[r] - Log[1 + r^2]/r == Pi/3, {r, 1}, WorkingPrecision -> 120]][[1]]
%o A395597 (PARI) solve(r = 1, 2, 2*atan(r) - log(1 + r^2)/r - Pi/3)
